      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775656399466,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "● # of queries processed,\n● total processing time across all queries,\n● the minimum query time (for a single query),\n● the median query time,\n● the average query time,\n● and the maximum query time.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "● # of queries processed,\n● total processing time across all queries,\n● the minimum query time (for a single query),\n● the median query time,\n● the average query time,\n● and the maximum query time.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "L-Qzo3-p0AOtnQ2ueKx1N",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -13.25077659921601,
      "y": 863.1478950560892,
      "width": 880.5431518554688,
      "height": 340,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2084397440,
      "version": 617,
      "versionNonce": 1580639872,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776086118772,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "constraints\n- The tool should gracefully handle files that are **larger** than the one given, \nand should not wait to start processing queries until all input is consumed.\n- Each query should then be executed by one of the concurrent workers your tool creates, with\nthe constraint that queries for the same hostname be executed by the same worker each time.\n  - each worker can execute from multiple hostnames. \n    - hostname -> worker mapping needed\n- Handles any invalid input appropriately.\n\nconstraints from questions\n- You need to implement it so that the files potentially exceed the machine's memory capacity.\n\n>\"total processing time\" is that wall-clock time of the entire execution, or the aggregate duration of all queries?\nAggregate duration.\n\n> \"query time\" is it the timer start strictly at the database driver's execution call\nIt should capture the full round-trip (send query + execute + transfer results + read rows).",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "constraints\n- The tool should gracefully handle files that are **larger** than the one given, \nand should not wait to start processing queries until all input is consumed.\n- Each query should then be executed by one of the concurrent workers your tool creates, with\nthe constraint that queries for the same hostname be executed by the same worker each time.\n  - each worker can execute from multiple hostnames. \n    - hostname -> worker mapping needed\n- Handles any invalid input appropriately.\n\nconstraints from questions\n- You need to implement it so that the files potentially exceed the machine's memory capacity.\n\n>\"total processing time\" is that wall-clock time of the entire execution, or the aggregate duration of all queries?\nAggregate duration.\n\n> \"query time\" is it the timer start strictly at the database driver's execution call\nIt should capture the full round-trip (send query + execute + transfer results + read rows).",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
