      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "questions:\n- do i need to handle some for of load balancing if workers are getting jammed\nwith work?\n- what does it mean to not stop reading/inputing data?\n- 'total processing time' is that wall-clock time of the entire execution, or the\naggregate duration of all queries? i assume the latter",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "questions:\n- do i need to handle some for of load balancing if workers are getting jammed with work?\n- what does it mean to not stop reading/inputing data?\n- 'total processing time' is that wall-clock time of the entire execution, or the aggregate duration of all queries? i assume the latter",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
